description.narrative: UNICEF reached over 204,865 people (61,459 males, 143,406 females) aged 10 years and above in 6 districts affected by floods, with integrated messages to maintain positive social behaviors through radio, community dialogue, interpersonal communication by teachers and volunteers, action theater and road shows. Consultations with communities affected by Cyclone Idai during the recovery phase has informed a new community engagement for C4D strategy that will be implemented in 2020. The Journey of Life community mobilization has commenced in 4 districts to adopt positive behaviours in the best interests of the child, as part of the Spotlight Initiative. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/12/2019
